   <pb facs="47"/>
   <head>The Author to the <hi>Reader.</hi>
   </head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">B</seg>Eing ouer intreated at this time to pub<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>lish this Sermon, and hauing my selfe so manie necessarie imploy<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ments otherwise, I was constrai<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ned to send vnto the Printer, that one and only vnperfect co<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>py which I had thereof; wher<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>in if (by reason of mine owne absence) there happen to be many faults, the Christian and
<pb facs="48"/> well disposed Reader, I hope, wil charitably censure them. As for the carping companions of our time, as I neuer desired to please them, so doe I not now seeke to satis<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fie them.</p>
   <pb facs="48"/>
